{"cursor":"2072","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"A 'French curve' is a template made out of metal, wood or plastic composed of\nmany different curves. It is used in manual drafting to draw smooth curves of\nvarying radii. The shapes are segments of the Euler spiral or clothoid curve.\n\nThe curve is placed on the drawing material, and a pencil, knife or other\nimplement is traced around its curves to produce the desired result.\n","linknr":121,"url":"French_curve","recorded":1362552595,"links":28,"instances":[],"pdf":[],"categories":["Technical drawing","Curves","Mathematical tools"],"headings":["Modern successors","See also","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0c/Krzywiki.jpg/87px-Krzywiki.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/60/L-Zeichnen2.png/88px-L-Zeichnen2.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/61/Curve_stencils.jpg/120px-Curve_stencils.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[],"members":[],"related":["Metal","Wood","Plastic","Curve","Euler_spiral","Pencil","Knife","CAD","Radius","BÃ©zier_spline","Ludwig_Burmester","Lexikon_der_gesamten_Technik","Ludwig_Burmester","Hyperbolas","Ellipse","Parabolas","Technical_drawing_tools"]}